<item>
            <title>[LU-6160] all test builds should enable SPL/ZFS debugging</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6160</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;ASSERTs in SPL/ZFS are off by default. It&apos;d be a good idea to enable SPL/ZFS assertions at least for test builds, which&apos;d pinpoint problems much earlier before they manifest as hard-to-diagnose symptoms.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have a patch that enables SPL/ZFS debugging:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/13431/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/13431/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But there&apos;s build failures for i686 in SPL/ZFS. So upstream SPL/ZFS would need a fix for that.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
